<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005-08-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Performance of Single-Step Gel-Based Reverse Transcription-PCR (RT-PCR) Assays Equivalent to That of Real-Time RT-PCR Assays for Detection of the Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome-Associated Coronavirus</TITLE><BODY>Simple gel-based one-step reverse transcription-PCR (RT-PCR) assays, used to investigate patients during the 2003 severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) outbreak in Singapore, were found to be as sensitive as commercial and in-house real-time RT-PCR assays. The detection limit was approximately 1 genome equivalent (GE) per 5 μl PCR mixture. One PFU of SARS coronavirus was estimated to be 258 ± 46 GE.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>